The notifications on my smartphone are turned off. It doesn't ring when I receive a call, and it doesn't vibrate or light up. [l][r]
I only tracked notifications and call history when I secretly went out to buy food or daily necessities. [l][r]
I could have watched it in the bathroom, but if I was too late, Chi-chan would have found out. [l][r]
[r] I want Chi-chan to talk as much as possible, read lots of her favorite books and tell her stories, tire her out, and let her sleep soundly. [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
During that time, it was my daily routine to go shopping at the convenience store and then go home, feeling truly grateful for the people who worked 24 hours a day without rest. [l][r]
[r]I asked my father, who is now back home in Hungary, for money. I notified my school that I was taking a leave of absence. I quit my part-time job. [l][r]
Everyone was worried about me. I apologized. [l][r]
[r]...Just a little longer, just a little longer please. [l][r]
I only think like that when I'm out, and when I get back to my room I don't think about it anymore. [l][r]

[cm]A life that can't last forever. [l][r]
But I wasn't scared. I think Chi-chan was probably more scared. So, I wasn't scared. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

