"Hello, is this Yuri?" [l][r]
"Kanazawa... Yes, it's me. It's been a while." [l][r]
"Oh yeah. That's right... [r]
How have you been?"[l][r]
[r] Kanazawa's voice rings in my ear. Hmm... It's been a while since I've heard that voice, but why does it feel like I've heard it a lot recently? [l][r]
[r] "Hmm... I wonder?" [l][r]
For some reason, I can't bring myself to lie and say "I'm fine," so I end up saying what I really think. [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"...I heard from Ishii-san that Chito seems to be a little weak." [l][r]
"Well, you should have said that before. ...Well, it's not really that big of a deal...but..." [l][r]
[r] Oh, this is bad. I think I could get away with it if I met Kanazawa in person, but it doesn't work on the phone. [l] My voice is getting a little hoarse. My words get stuck... [l][r]
[r]「…………」[l][r]
Kanazawa doesn't say anything. What's wrong? I wish he'd at least give me some kind of response. [l][r]
"So, what? I'm in a hurry."
"...Ah, sorry. But, if you're in a hurry, let's do it next time." [l][r]

[_tb_end_text]

[cm  ]
[tb_start_text mode=3 ]
"No, it's okay. ... I'm sorry too. Please tell me." [r]
"Is it okay...?" [l][r]
[r] Kanazawa spoke in a modest voice. An image of a kind-looking, gentle-looking man who could easily be persuaded by someone younger than me came to mind, with a slightly troubled look on his face. [l][r]
[r] "Yeah..." [l][r]
"Well, let's get straight to the point. We've found the Kettenkrad." [l][r]
"Huh?" [l][r]
"It's a Kettenkrad. It's your vehicle." [l][r]
[_tb_end_text]

